",[68,291,293],{"class":70,"line":292},14,[68,294,250],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":249},[68,296,298,300,303,305,308,310,312,315],{"class":70,"line":297},15,[68,299,75],{"class":74},[68,301,302],{"class":78}," e ",[68,304,82],{"class":74},[68,306,307],{"class":74}," new",[68,309,259],{"class":98},[68,311,102],{"class":78},[68,313,314],{"class":105},"'Jane'",[68,316,317],{"class":78},");\n",[68,319,321,323,325,327,330,332,334],{"class":70,"line":320},16,[68,322,95],{"class":78},[68,324,99],{"class":98},[68,326,102],{"class":78},[68,328,329],{"class":105},"'e: '",[68,331,109],{"class":74},[68,333,112],{"class":74},[68,335,336],{"class":78},"(e));\n",[68,338,340,342,344,347,349,351],{"class":70,"line":339},17,[68,341,95],{"class":78},[68,343,99],{"class":98},[68,345,346],{"class":78},"(e ",[68,348,30],{"class":74},[68,350,259],{"class":265},[68,352,317],{"class":78},[68,354,356,358,360,362,365,367,369,371,374],{"class":70,"line":355},18,[68,357,95],{"class":78},[68,359,99],{"class":98},[68,361,102],{"class":78},[68,363,364],{"class":105},"'undefined: '",[68,366,109],{"class":74},[68,368,112],{"class":74},[68,370,102],{"class":78},[68,372,373],{"class":85},"undefined",[68,375,376],{"class":78},"));\n",[68,378,380,382,384,386,389,391,393,395,398],{"class":70,"line":379},19,[68,381,95],{"class":78},[68,383,99],{"class":98},[68,385,102],{"class":78},[68,387,388],{"class":105},"'null: '",[68,390,109],{"class":74},[68,392,112],{"class":74},[68,394,102],{"class":78},[68,396,397],{"class":85},"null",[68,399,376],{"class":78},[17,401,402],{},"Before you scroll down, take a second to guess what each type is. Jot it down, then check the answer.",[17,404,405],{},[406,407],"img",{"alt":408,"src":409},"console output","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FcQ2BGpx.png",[17,411,412],{},"Most of it is fine, but this part is where things get a little off.",[17,414,415],{},[406,416],{"alt":417,"src":418},"array typeof output","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fk6yMxfJ.png",[17,420,421,422,425,426,429],{},"An empty array doesn't show up as ",[21,423,424],{},"Array",". So how do we actually tell whether something is an array? This is where you have to use ",[21,427,428],{},"Object","'s prototype to verify it — that's the way to see that it really is an array.",[17,431,432],{},[406,433],{"alt":434,"src":435},"Object prototype toString check","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FAFaoq5S.png",[17,437,438,439,441],{},"This is a pretty special spot, so I pulled the empty array aside to play with it. If the array isn't empty anymore and actually has data in it, will ",[21,440,23],{}," still report it as an object type?",[59,443,445],{"className":61,"code":444,"language":63,"meta":64,"style":64},"var d = ['Ray', 'Jack'];\nconsole.log('d: ' + typeof(d));\n",[21,446,447,470],{"__ignoreMap":64},[68,448,449,451,453,455,458,461,464,467],{"class":70,"line":71},[68,450,75],{"class":74},[68,452,189],{"class":78},[68,454,82],{"class":74},[68,456,457],{"class":78}," [",[68,459,460],{"class":105},"'Ray'",[68,462,463],{"class":78},", ",[68,465,466],{"class":105},"'Jack'",[68,468,469],{"class":78},"];\n",[68,471,472,474,476,478,480,482,484],{"class":70,"line":92},[68,473,95],{"class":78},[68,475,99],{"class":98},[68,477,102],{"class":78},[68,479,206],{"class":105},[68,481,109],{"class":74},[68,483,112],{"class":74},[68,485,213],{"class":78},[17,487,488],{},[406,489],{"alt":490,"src":491},"non-empty array typeof output","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F0IALYHW.png",[17,493,494,495,498,499,506],{},"The answer is the same. So as I mentioned in an earlier chapter, ",[40,496,497],{},"an array is an object",". How do you verify that? Flip through ",[500,501,505],"a",{"href":502,"rel":503},"https:\u002F\u002Fdeveloper.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Fdocs\u002FWeb\u002FJavaScript\u002FReference\u002FGlobal_Objects\u002FArray",[504],"nofollow","MDN"," and you'll see it.",[17,508,509],{},[406,510],{"alt":511,"src":512},"MDN Array reference","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fll4LAXg.png",[17,514,515,516,518],{},"So from this we know that in JavaScript ",[40,517,497],{},". That's important.",[17,520,521,522,524,525,528,529,31],{},"Next, ",[21,523,30],{},". This one basically tells us whether an object sits somewhere on the prototype chain. If it does, it returns ",[21,526,527],{},"true","; if not, ",[21,530,531],{},"false",[17,533,534,535,537,538,540,541,543],{},"Then there's ",[21,536,373],{},". ",[21,539,373],{}," is a special keyword in JavaScript, so it just returns ",[21,542,373],{}," — no surprise there.",[17,545,546,547,549],{},"And finally ",[21,548,397],{},". In the course the instructor calls this one JavaScript's all-time bug, which is why you get a result like this.",[17,551,552],{},[406,553],{"alt":554,"src":555},"typeof null output","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FonK6DL1.png",[12,557,559],{"id":558},"image-source","Image Source",[17,561,562],{},[500,563,566],{"href":564,"rel":565},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.udemy.com\u002Fjavascriptjs\u002F",[504],"JavaScript 全攻略:克服 JS 奇怪的部分",[568,569,570],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html pre.shiki code .s_sBn, html code.shiki .s_sBn{--shiki-default:#FFB757}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":64,"searchDepth":92,"depth":92,"links":572},[573,574,575],{"id":14,"depth":92,"text":15},{"id":34,"depth":92,"text":35},{"id":558,"depth":92,"text":559},"JsWeirdWorld","2019-05-24 14:55:00","We already know JavaScript is a dynamically typed language. That lets us do some pretty special things, but it's also dangerous. Normally when we want to know a variable's type, we reach for typeof — but honestly that method isn't great. So this chapter walks through typeof and instanceof, and how to actually figure out what something is.","md","en",{},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002Fjs-weird-world-59-typeof-instanceof","2",{"title":6,"description":578},false,"en\u002FJsWeirdWorld\u002Fjs-weird-world-59-typeof-instanceof",[588,589],"JavaScript","JavaScript 全攻略:克服JS奇怪的部分",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fjs-weird-world-59-typeof-instanceof\u002F","D1BbY6vBxwxXMpLLE_JBWNdd0tvBRsoQeYX2QwvfMvQ",{"newer":594,"older":598},{"url":595,"title":596,"date":597},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fjs-weird-world-60-strict-mode\u002F","[JS Weird World] No.60 Strict Mode: Make JavaScript Stop Covering for Your Typos","2019-05-24 15:34:00",{"url":599,"title":600,"date":601},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fjs-weird-world-58-initialization\u002F","[JS Weird World] No.58 Initialization","2019-05-24 13:34:00",[603,608,613],{"url":604,"title":605,"date":606,"readingMinutes":607},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F27\u002Fjs-weird-world-bonus-closures\u002F","[JS Weird World] Bonus: Closures, One More Time","2019-05-27 13:50:04","5",{"url":609,"title":610,"date":611,"readingMinutes":612},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F25\u002Fjs-weird-world-68-the-end-is-a-new-beginning\u002F","[JS Weird World] No.68 Wrapping Up the Weird Parts of JavaScript","2019-05-25 16:36:00","1",{"url":614,"title":615,"date":616,"readingMinutes":583},"\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F25\u002Fjs-weird-world-67-adding-jqu